                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-361-victim1951 t18280911-361-viclabel1865"></join>. On the 9th of August I lost a pot, but did not miss it till I saw it at Bow-street - this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-361-person1952">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BERRYMAN LUSH
               <interp inst="t18280911-361-person1952" type="surname" value="BERRYMAN LUSH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-361-person1952" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-361-person1952" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner is my son: I live in St. Giles', near the workhouse. I met him with this pot, and asked him how he came by it - he first said it was thrown at him by a boy, and then said it was given him to go and sell; I gave him in charge.</p>
